SIMPLE: entirely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entirely
<hw>En*tire"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an entire
manner; wholly; completely; fully; <as>as, the trace is
<ex>entirely</ex> lost</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Euphrates falls not <qex>entirely</qex> into the Persian Sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without alloy or mixture; truly;
sincerely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To highest God <qex>entirely</qex> pray.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entireness</ent>⟦br⟧
